  	<title>Environment</title>
  
  	<table>
  		<title>ENVIRONMENT</title>
  		<tgroup cols="4" align="left" colsep="1" rowsep="1">
  			<thead>
  				<row>
  					<entry align="center">Parameter Name</entry>
  					<entry align="center">Data Type</entry>
  					<entry align="center">Possible Values</entry>
  					<entry align="center">Default</entry>	
  				</row>
  			</thead>
  			<tbody>
  				<row>
  					<entry>ENVIRONMENT</entry>
  					<entry>String</entry>
  					<entry>
  						<itemizedlist>
  							<listitem>
  								<para>
  									AUT
  								</para>
  							</listitem>
  							<listitem>
  								<para>
  									ITE
  								</para>
  							</listitem>
  						</itemizedlist>
  					</entry>
  					<entry>AUT</entry>
  				</row>
  			</tbody>
  		</tgroup>
  	</table>
  	<itemizedlist>
  		<listitem>
  			<para>
  				Set this parameter to <emphasis>AUT</emphasis> when your tests are e.g. executed on only 
  				one machine, i.e. ITE/Testexec, AUT Agent, AUT and the external command can all be found on the 
  				same machine.
  			</para>
  		</listitem>
  		<listitem>
  			<para>
  				Set this parameter to ITE when your external AUT Agent and the AUT run on a different machine
  				than the ITE/Testexec and the external command be found on the machine on which the AUT is
  				running. 
  			</para>
  		</listitem>
  	</itemizedlist>
